## Third-Party Licenses

This project includes or depends on the following third-party works:

### Hanzi Writer
- Repository: https://github.com/chanind/hanzi-writer
- License: MIT
- Used for: SVG stroke order rendering and animations

### hanzi_lookup
- Repository: https://github.com/gugray/hanzi_lookup
- License: LGPL-3.0
- Used for: Handwriting recognition (compiled to WebAssembly)
- The source code for hanzi_lookup is available at the repository above.
  The COPYING and COPYING.LESSER files from LGPL-3.0 apply to the hanzi_lookup component.

### Make Me a Hanzi (stroke data)
- Repository: https://github.com/skishore/makemeahanzi
- License: Arphic Public License
- Used for: Character stroke order data
- The stroke data was originally extracted from fonts by Arphic Technology,
  a Taiwanese font foundry that released their work under the
  Arphic Public License in 1999.

### CC-CEDICT (dictionary data)
- Website: https://cc-cedict.org/wiki/
- License: CC BY-SA 4.0 (Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0)
- Used for: Chinese-English dictionary definitions (public/dict.json)
- CC-CEDICT is maintained by MDBG. The data file is included as a
  derived work under the ShareAlike terms.
